{
    "blocks": [
        {
            "id": "intro_variables",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "Creating Variables",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 1
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Variables are like containers that store information. They let you save data and use it later in your program. Think of them as labeled boxes where you can put things."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "what_are_variables",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "What are Variables?",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 2
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "A **variable** is a name that refers to a value. You can store different types of data in variables: text, numbers, and more."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "# Creating a variable\nname = \"Alice\"\nprint(name)",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "caption": "Your first variable",
                        "output": "Alice"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Here, `name` is the variable, and `\"Alice\"` is the value stored in it. The `=` sign assigns the value to the variable."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "variable_basics",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "You can create variables to store different types of information:"
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "# Store text (strings)\nmessage = \"Hello World\"\n\n# Store numbers\nage = 25\n\n# Store decimal numbers\nheight = 5.6\n\nprint(message)\nprint(age)\nprint(height)",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "caption": "Different types of variables",
                        "output": "Hello World\n25\n5.6"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quick_check_basic_variables",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "code_fill",
                    "content": "Fill in the **equals sign** to create the variable `city`.",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "lines": [
                            {
                                "code": "city {1} \"New York\"",
                                "indent": 0,
                                "blank": "1"
                            },
                            {
                                "code": "print(city)",
                                "indent": 0
                            }
                        ],
                        "options": [
                            "="
                        ],
                        "solutions": {
                            "1": "="
                        },
                        "hint": "Use the equals sign to assign the value to the variable",
                        "correctFeedback": "Perfect! The **=** sign assigns values to variables.",
                        "incorrectFeedback": "Use **=** to assign the value to the variable",
                        "explanation": "The equals sign (=) assigns values to variables.",
                        "output": "New York"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quick_check_using_variables",
            "elements": [
                {
